          "level": 3,
          "body": "**Câu 51:** The new accounting software ____ by all departments since January.\n- A. has been used\n- B. has used\n- C. is used\n- D. was used\n\n**Câu 52:** The committee ____ meeting every Thursday at 10 AM to discuss policy changes.\n- A. is being\n- B. was being\n- C. has been being\n- D. is\n\n**Câu 53:** By the time the new regulations ____ into effect, the company will have prepared all necessary documentation.\n- A. come\n- B. came\n- C. will come\n- D. have come\n\n**Câu 54:** The regional manager ____ a presentation on market expansion at the annual conference.\n- A. delivered\n- B. has delivered\n- C. had delivered\n- D. will have delivered\n\n**Câu 55:** Several major infrastructure projects ____ in the city center over the past decade.\n- A. have completed\n- B. have been completed\n- C. had been completed\n- D. was completed\n\n**Câu 56:** The travel department ____ employees to submit expense reports by the end of each month.\n- A. required\n- B. requires\n- C. is requiring\n- D. has required\n\n**Câu 57:** While the technical team ____ the system upgrade, the users experienced intermittent disruptions.\n- A. performs\n- B. was performing\n- C. has performed\n- D. had performed\n\n**Câu 58:** The firm ____ its investment in renewable energy over the past five years.\n- A. has increased\n- B. increased\n- C. had increased\n- D. was increasing\n\n**Câu 59:** ____ the annual financial report been audited yet?\n- A. Have\n- B. Has\n- C. Did\n- D. Had\n\n**Câu 60:** The HR director ____ employees about the new benefits package next week.\n- A. will inform\n- B. informs\n- C. informed\n- D. has informed\n\n**Câu 61:** The customer service team ____ over 500 calls daily during peak season.\n- A. handles\n- B. handled\n- C. has handled\n- D. is handling\n\n**Câu 62:** Before Ms. Chen ____ the department, she had managed three other divisions.\n- A. took over\n- B. takes over\n- C. has taken over\n- D. had taken over\n\n**Câu 63:** The company ____ its headquarters to a new location next spring.\n- A. will move\n- B. moves\n- C. is moving\n- D. A hoặc C\n\n**Câu 64:** The payroll department ____ the employees' salaries every month on the 25th.\n- A. processes\n- B. processed\n- C. has processed\n- D. is processing\n\n**Câu 65:** Since the merger, the company ____ its global workforce significantly.\n- A. expands\n- B. has expanded\n- C. expanded\n- D. had expanded\n\n**Câu 66:** The legal team ____ the contract before it was signed by both parties.\n- A. reviewed\n- B. has reviewed\n- C. had reviewed\n- D. A hoặc C\n\n**Câu 67:** ____ the board approved the strategic plan at its last meeting?\n- A. Does\n- B. Did\n- C. Has\n- D. Had\n\n**Câu 68:** The sales manager ____ the quarterly targets for the past three consecutive years.\n- A. has met\n- B. has been meeting\n- C. meets\n- D. had met\n\n**Câu 69:** The project team ____ on the new product design since the beginning of the quarter.\n- A. works\n- B. worked\n- C. has been working\n- D. had been working\n\n**Câu 70:** The annual report ____ to shareholders next month.\n- A. will distribute\n- B. will be distributed\n- C. is distributing\n- D. distributes\n\n**Câu 71:** Mr. Davis, who ____ as CFO for ten years, announced his retirement yesterday.\n- A. serves\n- B. served\n- C. has served\n- D. is serving\n\n**Câu 72:** By the end of this month, the company ____ the entire network infrastructure.\n- A. upgrades\n- B. upgraded\n- C. will have upgraded\n- D. will upgrade\n\n**Câu 73:** The marketing department ____ several successful campaigns this year.\n- A. has launched\n- B. launched\n- C. had launched\n- D. is launching\n\n**Câu 74:** The building ____ currently to accommodate the growing staff.\n- A. renovates\n- B. is being renovated\n- C. has been renovated\n- D. was renovated\n\n**Câu 75:** ____ your company ever ____ business with overseas suppliers before?\n- A. Has ... done\n- B. Have ... done\n- C. Did ... do\n- D. Had ... done\n\n**Câu 76:** The committee ____ the applications for three weeks before making a final decision.\n- A. reviewed\n- B. has reviewed\n- C. had been reviewing\n- D. has been reviewing\n\n**Câu 77:** The prototype ____ in the laboratory since early March for extensive testing.\n- A. is being tested\n- B. has been tested\n- C. has been being tested\n- D. has been testing\n\n**Câu 78:** The company ____ the new regulations in response to recent industry changes.\n- A. adopts\n- B. adopted\n- C. has adopted\n- D. A hoặc B\n\n**Câu 79:** We ____ the facilities manager to oversee the office relocation next month.\n- A. hired\n- B. have hired\n- C. had hired\n- D. will have hired\n\n**Câu 80:** ____ the project timeline been extended due to the unexpected delays?\n- A. Have\n- B. Has\n- C. Did\n- D. Was\n\n**Câu 81:** The CEO ____ a comprehensive restructuring plan since the company faced financial difficulties.\n- A. implements\n- B. implemented\n- C. has been implementing\n- D. had implemented\n\n**Câu 82:** The accounting department ____ all invoices at the end of each business day.\n- A. processes\n- B. is processing\n- C. has processed\n- D. processes\n\n**Câu 83:** By the time the auditor arrived, the finance team ____ the financial statements.\n- A. completed\n- B. has completed\n- C. had completed\n- D. was completing\n\n**Câu 84:** The airline ____ direct flights to Tokyo since last summer.\n- A. operated\n- B. operates\n- C. has operated\n- D. is operating\n\n**Câu 85:** The regional office ____ to the new business district in October.\n- A. moved\n- B. moves\n- C. will move\n- D. is moving\n\n**Câu 86:** The customer feedback form ____ available online since the product launch.\n- A. is\n- B. has been\n- C. was\n- D. had been\n\n**Câu 87:** The technical support team ____ the issue before the user called for escalation.\n- A. resolved\n- B. has resolved\n- C. had resolved\n- D. resolves\n\n**Câu 88:** The conference registration ____ at 5 PM on the day before the event.\n- A. closes\n- B. closed\n- C. will close\n- D. A hoặc B\n\n**Câu 89:** Over the past decade, the company ____ its environmental sustainability initiatives significantly.\n- A. expanded\n- B. has expanded\n- C. had expanded\n- D. was expanding\n\n**Câu 90:** The board of directors ____ a press release regarding the merger once all details ____ finalized.\n- A. issued ... were\n- B. will issue ... have been\n- C. A hoặc B\n- D. has issued ... have been\n\n**Câu 91:** The firm ____ in compliance with industry regulations since its establishment.\n- A. has been\n- B. is\n- C. was\n- D. had been\n\n**Câu 92:** The shipment ____ yesterday morning and should arrive at the warehouse tomorrow.\n- A. shipped\n- B. was shipped\n- C. has shipped\n- D. had been shipped\n\n**Câu 93:** The assistant ____ the meeting minutes while the manager ____ the presentation.\n- A. was taking ... was giving\n- B. took ... gave\n- C. has taken ... has given\n- D. was taking ... gave\n\n**Câu 94:** The website currently ____ more than 10,000 visitors daily.\n- A. attracts\n- B. attracted\n- C. has attracted\n- D. is attracting\n\n**Câu 95:** The company ____ its operations in Africa when the political situation stabilized.\n- A. expanded\n- B. has expanded\n- C. expands\n- D. was expanding\n\n**Câu 96:** The training sessions ____ for new employees every Monday morning.\n- A. is held\n- B. are held\n- C. has been held\n- D. will be held\n\n**Câu 97:** By the end of this year, the firm ____ a total of 25 new products to the market.\n- A. launched\n- B. has launched\n- C. will have launched\n- D. launches\n\n**Câu 98:** The project manager ____ the budget allocation before the fiscal year ends.\n- A. finalizes\n- B. finalized\n- C. will finalize\n- D. A hoặc C\n\n**Câu 99:** The HR department ____ a series of professional development workshops since last autumn.\n- A. offered\n- B. has offered\n- C. had offered\n- D. has been offering\n\n**Câu 100:** The chairman's annual address ____ broadcast live on the company's website at noon.\n- A. is\n- B. was\n- C. will be\n- D. has been\n\n---"
